(1) Hague Street, west from Pearl Street to the Brooklyn Bridge. On the right (north side), is a 2-story garage known as No. 369 Pearl Street, which also bears Nos. 1-3 Hague Street; beyond same, are 5 and 4-story warehouses (Nos. 7-9 Hague Street). On the opposite side (south side) from fore to background are; No. 367 Pearl Street (5-story tenement), Nos. 6-4 (double 3 1/2-story building) and No. 2 Hague Street (6-story building).

October 25, 1927.

P. L. Sperr.

(2) The same.

March 20, 1936.

P. L. Sperr.

(3) A closer view of Nos. 4-6 and 2. The anchorage shown is that of the Brooklyn Bridge.

March 20, 1936.

P. L. Sperr.

355-357 Pearl Street, west side, north of the Brooklyn Bridge, of which a portion appears on the left. Note the Franklin Square Station of the Second and Third Aves., Elevated on Pearl Street.

March 20, 1936.

P. L. Sperr.

ASSUMING STREET TO BE NORTH AND SOUTH
